    faq: { title: 'Frequently Asked Questions', subtitle: 'Find answers to common questions about SkinGuard AI', searchPlaceholder: 'Search FAQs...', gettingStarted: 'Getting Started', featuresAccuracy: 'Features & Accuracy', privacySecurity: 'Privacy & Security', subscriptionsBilling: 'Subscriptions & Billing', melanomaSkinHealth: 'Melanoma & Skin Health', technicalSupport: 'Technical Support', ctaTitle: 'Still have questions?', ctaSubtitle: "Can't find the answer you're looking for? Please contact our support team.", ctaBtn: 'Contact Us', noResults: 'No questions found matching your search.', clearSearch: 'Clear search', gs_q1: 'What is SkinGuard AI?', gs_a1: 'SkinGuard AI is an advanced AI-powered skin health monitoring application that helps you track moles and skin lesions from home. Using 94% accurate AI analysis based on dermatological ABCDE criteria, it provides insights into potential skin changes and alerts you to suspicious developments.', gs_q2: 'Do I need a dermatologist to use SkinGuard AI?', gs_a2: 'No, SkinGuard AI is designed for personal use and doesn\'t require a dermatologist. However, we always recommend consulting a qualified dermatologist for medical advice and professional diagnosis. SkinGuard AI is a monitoring and tracking tool, not a medical diagnostic device.', gs_q3: 'How do I get started?', gs_a3: 'Simply download the app, create an account, and start taking photos of your moles and skin lesions. The app will guide you through the process with on-screen instructions. You can start with the free Essentials plan to explore all basic features.', gs_q4: 'Is SkinGuard AI available on all devices?', gs_a4: 'Yes, SkinGuard AI works on iOS, Android, and web browsers. You can seamlessly switch between devices and all your data syncs automatically.', fa_q1: 'How accurate is the AI analysis?', fa_a1: 'SkinGuard AI achieves 94% accuracy in detecting potential skin changes using the ABCDE criteria (Asymmetry, Border irregularity, Color variation, Diameter, and Evolution). This accuracy is based on extensive training with dermatological datasets. However, it should not replace professional medical diagnosis.', fa_q2: 'What does the ABCDE analysis mean?', fa_a2: 'ABCDE is a dermatological screening method: A=Asymmetry (uneven shape), B=Border irregularity, C=Color variation, D=Diameter (larger than a pencil eraser), E=Evolution (changes over time). SkinGuard AI analyzes your photos against these criteria to flag potential concerns.', fa_q3: 'Can I track multiple body areas?', fa_a3: 'Yes! SkinGuard AI includes an interactive body map where you can mark and track moles and lesions across different body areas. This helps you organize your monitoring and track changes systematically.', fa_q4: 'How often should I take photos?', fa_a4: 'We recommend taking photos monthly or whenever you notice changes. Regular monitoring helps establish a baseline and makes it easier to detect subtle changes over time. The app will remind you based on your preference.', ps_q1: 'Is my data secure?', ps_a1: 'Yes. In the Essentials plan, all data is stored locally on your device and never leaves your browser. Pro and Pro Plus users get encrypted cloud backup with military-grade encryption (AES-256). We never share your data with third parties.', ps_q2: 'Can I export my data?', ps_a2: 'Yes! Pro and Pro Plus users can export their data as PDF or CSV files. This is useful for sharing with your dermatologist or for personal records.', ps_q3: 'What happens to my photos?', ps_a3: 'Your photos are processed locally on your device (Essentials plan) or encrypted in our secure cloud (Pro/Pro Plus). We use them only for AI analysis and never share them with anyone without your explicit consent.', ps_q4: 'Is SkinGuard AI HIPAA compliant?', ps_a4: 'While SkinGuard AI implements security best practices similar to HIPAA standards, it is not a medical device and is not officially HIPAA certified. For sensitive medical data, consult your healthcare provider.', sb_q1: "What's the difference between plans?", sb_a1: 'Essentials (Free): Basic monitoring with local storage. Pro ($9.99/month): Advanced AI analysis, cloud backup, detailed reports. Pro Plus ($49/year): All Pro features plus priority support and multi-user management.', sb_q2: 'Can I cancel my subscription?', sb_a2: 'Absolutely! You can cancel anytime with no questions asked. Your data remains accessible, and you\'ll revert to the Essentials plan features.', sb_q3: 'Is there a free trial?', sb_a3: 'Yes! The Essentials plan is completely free and includes all basic monitoring features. Upgrade to Pro or Pro Plus anytime to unlock advanced features.', sb_q4: 'How do I upgrade my plan?', sb_a4: "You can upgrade directly in the app settings. Your upgrade takes effect immediately, and you'll have access to all premium features. If you're on a monthly plan, you can switch to annual anytime.", ms_q1: 'Why is early melanoma detection important?', ms_a1: 'Melanoma is the most serious type of skin cancer. When detected early, the 5-year survival rate is over 99%. Delayed detection can significantly reduce survival rates. Regular monitoring with tools like SkinGuard AI helps catch changes early.', ms_q2: 'What are the warning signs of melanoma?', ms_a2: 'Watch for the ABCDE signs: Asymmetry, irregular Border, multiple Colors, Diameter larger than a pencil eraser, and Evolution (changes over time). Also watch for bleeding, itching, or pain. If you notice any of these, consult a dermatologist immediately.', ms_q3: 'Who should use SkinGuard AI?', ms_a3: "Anyone concerned about skin health can benefit from SkinGuard AI. It's especially useful for people with: fair skin, many moles, family history of melanoma, history of sunburns, or previous skin cancer. However, everyone can benefit from regular skin monitoring.", ms_q4: 'Can SkinGuard AI replace a dermatologist?', ms_a4: 'No. SkinGuard AI is a monitoring and tracking tool, not a replacement for professional medical care. We always recommend regular dermatologist visits, especially if you have risk factors for skin cancer.', ts_q1: 'What if the AI analysis seems incorrect?', ts_a1: 'AI is not perfect. If you believe an analysis is incorrect, please report it through the app. Our team reviews feedback to continuously improve accuracy. Always consult a dermatologist for professional diagnosis.', ts_q2: 'How do I contact support?', ts_a2: 'You can reach our support team via: info@skinguardai.app (general inquiries) or partners@skinguardai.app (partnerships). We aim to respond within 24 hours.', ts_q3: 'What if I forgot my password?', ts_a3: "Use the 'Forgot Password' option on the login screen. You'll receive an email with instructions to reset your password. Check your spam folder if you don't see it.", ts_q4: 'Does SkinGuard AI work offline?', ts_a4: 'Yes! The Essentials plan works completely offline. Pro and Pro Plus plans can work offline, but cloud sync requires an internet connection. Changes sync automatically when you reconnect.' },
